---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const discordUrl = 'https://discord.gg/your-server-here';
---

<BaseLayout title="Guidelines" description="How to use these scripts, licensing information, and terms">
  <div class="page-container">
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1 class="page-title">Guidelines</h1>
      <div class="ornamental-divider"></div>
    </header>

    <div class="page-content guidelines-content">

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq-controls">
        <button id="expand-all" class="faq-control-btn">Expand All</button>
        <button id="collapse-all" class="faq-control-btn">Collapse All</button>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-section">

        <h3>Before Recording</h3>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Do I need permission to record a script?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. All scripts are open-source and free to use. However, I ask that you notify me before recording by filling out the form on this website. This is not for approval - it's for record keeping.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">How do I let you know I'm recording?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Please fill out the recording notification form on this website twice: once when you plan to record, and once when you are about to publish (either right before or right after). Include all requested details, such as the script title, your name or channel, and where you plan to post.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I change the pronouns in the script?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. You may adjust pronouns to be specifically male, female, or gender-neutral. The change must not introduce sexist language. Please note your pronoun choice when filling out the form.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I make changes to the script?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Small word changes for flow or personal speech patterns are allowed, as long as the meaning remains unchanged. You may also change character names, provided they are not offensive, racist, or sexist.</p>
            <p><strong>You may not:</strong> Cut scenes, extend scenes, change the setting or scenario, or combine the script with another creator's work.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Do I have to follow the acting notes and SFX cues?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>These are recommendations to help you understand the script's intentions. It is not mandatory, but I encourage you to read them before recording - even if you choose to interpret things differently.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I collaborate with other voice actors on a script?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. For collaborations, the organizer should fill out the form and include the names of all participating voice actors.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I have someone contact you on my behalf?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. If an assistant or manager is reaching out on your behalf, please indicate this clearly in the form or message and include both names.</p></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Posting and Credit</h3>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Where can I post my recording?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>You may post on most platforms, including YouTube, Twitch, Patreon, and Bilibili. Recordings may not be posted on platforms primarily hosting explicit content.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">How should I credit you?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Please credit me as the script author and include a link to this website.</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Videos:</strong> Include credit in the description</li>
              <li><strong>Audio-only:</strong> Include it in the description or accompanying text</li>
              <li><strong>Social media:</strong> Include explicit credit in the caption</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Do I need to notify you after posting?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Please fill out the form again with the link to your posted recording. If your content is behind a paywall or requires account registration, please also send me a copy of the audio file via email or through the form.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I post the same recording on multiple platforms?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes, but only one copy of the same recording may exist on each platform at a time. If you wish to re-upload, the previous version must be removed first.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">What if my channel gets deleted or rebranded?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>If your previous recording on a platform is gone and you want to re-upload, please fill out the form again to notify me.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can someone else repost my recording?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Others may repost your recording with your permission. They must credit both you as the voice actor and me as the script author, following the same guidelines.</p></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Clips, Previews, and Additional Content</h3>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I post short clips or previews?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. You may post clips, previews, TikToks, YouTube Shorts, or similar short-form content. Credit is still required in the same manner as full recordings.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I include my recording in a compilation?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>You may include your recording in a compilation with your own content only. You may not include it in compilations with other creators' content. Credit is required.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can someone make a reaction video to my recording?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Reaction videos should follow your policy as the voice actor. This is between you and the reactor.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I add background music or extra sound effects?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. You may add background music, ambient sounds, or soundscapes beyond the SFX cues, provided they are generally in theme with the existing cues and mood of the script.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I add visuals to my recording?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>You may add static images or simple visuals to accompany your recording. Full animation or complete visual representation of the story falls under adaptation and requires consultation.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Do I need to include your name in thumbnails?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. You are free to design thumbnails and promotional images without including my name. However, any accompanying text (titles, descriptions, captions) must still include proper credit.</p></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Live Streaming and Other Formats</h3>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I perform the script on a live stream?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. You may perform scripts live on Twitch, YouTube Live, or similar platforms, as long as the platform does not primarily host explicit content. The same notification process applies - fill out the form before streaming and again after the VOD is posted. Credit is required in the same manner as full recordings.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can my recording be used as a TikTok sound?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Whether your recording is made available as a TikTok sound is your decision as the voice actor.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I perform the script on a podcast?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Performing a script as part of a podcast episode (not your own channel) requires prior consultation. Please contact me via email.</p></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Monetization</h3>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I monetize my recording?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. You may monetize on any platform that does not primarily host explicit content - this includes YouTube ads, Twitch streams, Patreon memberships, paid downloads, and similar. For any monetized content, you must include a link to this website. Sponsored content that features my script is not permitted.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I sell or monetize the script itself?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. The original script text and any PDF or document form of the script may not be sold, redistributed for payment, or monetized in any way. Only your original recording may be monetized.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I use the script for commercial projects?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Scripts may not be used for commercial projects beyond individual content creation (such as podcasts, apps, or audiobooks) without consulting me first. Please contact me via email to discuss.</p></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Accessibility and Captions</h3>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I add closed captions to my recording?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. You may add closed captions (synchronized within the video player, such as YouTube's CC feature). Captions may be clean verbatim - accurate to the spoken words with filler removed. You must still follow the standard crediting policy, including a link to this website.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I post a standalone transcript?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. Standalone transcripts - posted in the description, as a separate document, or anywhere outside the video player where text can be copied - are not permitted. This protects the script while still allowing accessibility through closed captions.</p></div>
        </div>

        <h3>What's Not Allowed</h3>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I translate the script into another language?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. I cannot guarantee the accuracy or meaning of translations.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I adapt the script into another format?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Adaptations (such as comics, full animations, or written stories) require consultation. Please contact me via email before proceeding.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I create derivative works based on your characters?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>These scripts are works of fiction without a continued storyline or established world. Please do not create derivative works (fan fiction, extended storylines, etc.) without letting me know first.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I use an AI voice to record the script?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. AI-generated or synthetic voices may not be used.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can the script be used to train AI models?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. Scripts may not be used to train any models, including audio, video, or text models.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can the script or recording be used for NFTs?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. Neither the script nor any recordings made from it may be used for NFTs.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I add mature or explicit content?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. You may not add profanity, sexual content, violence, or any content that would make the recording 18+ or NSFW.</p></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Content Warnings and Age Ratings</h3>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Should I include content warnings?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>I will include content warnings with each script that I ask you to respect. If you believe additional warnings are necessary for your audience, you may add them.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Should I include age ratings?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>I may provide suggested age framing, but it is your responsibility as the voice actor to understand your audience and determine if additional age warnings are appropriate.</p></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Series and Exclusivity</h3>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I request exclusive rights to a script?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>I am not currently taking commissions, so there are no exclusive recording rights available.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">If I record part one of a series, do I have priority for future parts?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. You are free to record any parts of a series, and there is no expectation from me that you will continue. Other voice actors may also record any parts independently.</p></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Recording Deletion and Archival</h3>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I delete my recording without notifying you?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. You are free to remove your recording at any time without notification.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can my recording be archived by third parties?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>I would prefer no third-party archival of my scripts or recordings made from them.</p></div>
        </div>

        <h3>Other Questions</h3>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Do I have to join the Discord server?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>No, but I encourage it. The Discord is a space for voice actors and fellow script writers to connect.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Do I need to engage with your work beyond crediting?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. I do not expect cross-promotion or additional engagement beyond the crediting requirements. Additional support is appreciated but never obligated.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">What happens if I break a guideline?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>I will contact you to request a correction. For major violations without response, I may request removal and issue a public notice.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">What if you remove or change a script after I've recorded it?</button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Existing recordings are not affected. You may keep your recording posted.</p></div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="ornamental-divider"></div>

      <h2>Complete Recording Guidelines</h2>

      <h3>Notification Requirements</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Before recording:</strong> Fill out the notification form on this website with all requested details.</li>
        <li><strong>Before or after posting:</strong> Fill out the form again with the link to your final posted recording.</li>
        <li><strong>Paywalled or restricted content:</strong> If your recording requires payment or account registration to access, send me a copy of the audio file via email or through the form.</li>
        <li><strong>Re-uploads:</strong> If your previous recording on a platform has been removed and you wish to re-upload, fill out the form again.</li>
        <li><strong>Representatives:</strong> If an assistant or manager is contacting me on your behalf, indicate this clearly and include both names.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>These notifications are for record-keeping, not permission or approval.</p>

      <hr class="section-divider" />

      <h3>Permitted Modifications</h3>
      <p><strong>You may:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Make small word changes for natural flow or personal speech patterns, provided the meaning is unchanged</li>
        <li>Change character names, provided they are not racist, sexist, or offensive (inside references meaningful to your community are acceptable)</li>
        <li>Adjust pronouns to be male, female, or gender-neutral, provided the change does not introduce sexist language</li>
        <li>Add background music, ambient sounds, or soundscapes that are in theme with the existing cues</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>You may not:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Cut, shorten, or extend any scenes</li>
        <li>Change the setting or scenario</li>
        <li>Combine the script with another creator's script</li>
        <li>Add lines beyond what is necessary for flow</li>
        <li>Change any wording to include profanity or offensive language</li>
        <li>Add sexual, violent, explicit, or NSFW content</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Please note any pronoun changes when filling out the form.</p>

      <hr class="section-divider" />

      <h3>Acting Notes and Sound Cues</h3>
      <p>Acting notes and SFX cues are included to communicate my intentions. They are recommendations, not requirements. I encourage you to read and understand them before recording, even if you choose to interpret the script differently.</p>

      <hr class="section-divider" />

      <h3>Credit and Attribution</h3>
      <p>All recordings must credit me as the script author.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Video content:</strong> Credit in the description box, with a link to this website</li>
        <li><strong>Audio-only content:</strong> Credit in the description or accompanying text, with a link to this website</li>
        <li><strong>Social media posts:</strong> Explicit credit in the caption, with a link to this website if possible</li>
        <li><strong>Clips and previews:</strong> Same credit requirements as full recordings</li>
        <li><strong>Thumbnails and promotional images:</strong> My name is not required in visuals, but must appear in accompanying text</li>
      </ul>
      <p>For monetized content, a link to this website is required.</p>

      <hr class="section-divider" />

      <h3>Clips, Compilations, and Additional Content</h3>
      <p><strong>Clips and previews:</strong> You may post short clips, previews, or short-form content (TikTok, YouTube Shorts, etc.) with proper credit.</p>
      <p><strong>Compilations:</strong> You may include your recording in compilations with your own content only. Compilations with other creators' content are not permitted.</p>
      <p><strong>Reaction videos:</strong> Follow the voice actor's policy regarding reactions.</p>
      <p><strong>Background music and sounds:</strong> You may add music, ambient sounds, or soundscapes that complement the existing cues and mood.</p>
      <p><strong>Visuals:</strong> Static images and simple visuals are permitted. Full animation or complete visual storytelling requires consultation as an adaptation.</p>
      <p><strong>TikTok sounds:</strong> Whether to make your recording available as a TikTok sound is your decision.</p>

      <hr class="section-divider" />

      <h3>Live Streaming</h3>
      <p>You may perform scripts live on streaming platforms (Twitch, YouTube Live, etc.), provided the platform does not primarily host explicit content. The same notification process applies: fill out the form before streaming and again after posting the VOD.</p>

      <hr class="section-divider" />

      <h3>Podcasts</h3>
      <p>Performing a script as part of a podcast episode (not your own channel) requires prior consultation. Contact me via email.</p>

      <hr class="section-divider" />

      <h3>Monetization</h3>
      <p><strong>Permitted:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Monetization on any platform that does not primarily host explicit content (YouTube ads, Twitch streams, Patreon memberships, paid downloads, and similar)</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Not permitted:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Selling, redistributing, or monetizing the script itself (text or PDF)</li>
        <li>Sponsored content featuring the script</li>
        <li>Commercial projects beyond individual content creation (podcasts, apps, audiobooks, etc.) without prior consultation</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Only your original recording may be monetized - not the script document in any form.</p>
      <p>For any monetized content, you must include a link to this website.</p>
      <p>For commercial use or adaptation inquiries, contact me via email. For standard recording notifications, please use the form on this website.</p>

      <hr class="section-divider" />

      <h3>Accessibility and Captions</h3>
      <p><strong>Closed captions:</strong> You may add closed captions synchronized within the video player (e.g., YouTube's CC feature). Captions may be clean verbatim - accurate to the spoken dialogue with filler words removed. Standard credit requirements apply.</p>
      <p><strong>Standalone transcripts:</strong> Not permitted. Transcripts posted in descriptions, as separate documents, or anywhere text can be freely copied are not allowed. This protects the script text while still allowing accessibility through in-player captions.</p>

      <hr class="section-divider" />

      <h3>Platform and Distribution</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Recordings may be posted on multiple platforms</li>
        <li>Recordings may not be posted on platforms primarily hosting explicit content</li>
        <li>Only one copy of the same recording may exist on a given platform at a time; re-uploads require removal of the previous version and a new form submission</li>
        <li>Others may repost your recording with your permission, following the same credit requirements</li>
      </ul>

      <hr class="section-divider" />

      <h3>Multiple Recordings and Collaborations</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Multiple voice actors may record the same script</li>
        <li>The same voice actor may record a script more than once; each recording requires a new form submission</li>
        <li>Collaborations are welcome; the organizer should fill out the form with all participating voice actors' names</li>
        <li>Recording part of a series does not create priority or expectation for future parts</li>
      </ul>

      <hr class="section-divider" />

      <h3>Series and Exclusivity</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>No exclusive recording rights are available at this time</li>
        <li>Voice actors may record any parts of a series independently</li>
        <li>There is no expectation to continue recording a series once started</li>
      </ul>

      <hr class="section-divider" />

      <h3>Translation and Adaptation</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Translation:</strong> Not permitted. I cannot guarantee the meaning of translations.</li>
        <li><strong>Adaptation:</strong> Adaptations into other formats (comics, full animation, written stories, etc.) require consultation. Contact me via email.</li>
        <li><strong>Derivative works:</strong> Please do not create derivative works based on characters or scenarios without letting me know first.</li>
      </ul>

      <hr class="section-divider" />

      <h3>AI, Synthetic Voices, and NFTs</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>AI-generated or synthetic voices may not be used to record scripts</li>
        <li>Scripts may not be used to train any AI models, including audio, video, or text models</li>
        <li>Neither scripts nor recordings may be used for NFTs</li>
      </ul>

      <hr class="section-divider" />

      <h3>Content Warnings and Age Ratings</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Scripts will include content warnings that I ask you to respect</li>
        <li>You may add additional content warnings if you feel they are necessary</li>
        <li>Age-appropriate framing is your responsibility based on your audience</li>
      </ul>

      <hr class="section-divider" />

      <h3>Recording Deletion and Archival</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>You may delete your recording at any time without notifying me</li>
        <li>I prefer no third-party archival of scripts or recordings</li>
        <li>If I remove or revise a script, existing recordings are not affected and may remain posted</li>
        <li>I retain the right to request removal of recordings that significantly violate these guidelines</li>
      </ul>

      <hr class="section-divider" />

      <h3>Guideline Violations</h3>
      <p>If a guideline is violated, I will contact you to request correction. For major violations without response, I may request removal and issue a public notice.</p>

      <div class="ornamental-divider"></div>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Recording notifications:</strong> Use the form on this website</li>
        <li><strong>General inquiries:</strong> Email or Discord</li>
        <li><strong>Adaptation, commercial use, or podcast inquiries:</strong> Email</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="contact-buttons">
        <a href={discordUrl} class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Join the Discord</a>
      </div>

      <div class="ornamental-divider"></div>

      <h2>Community</h2>
      <p>I encourage voice actors and script writers to join the Discord server. It's a space to connect, share, and support one another - though joining is not required.</p>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.guidelines-content {
  width: 100%;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

.guidelines-content h2 {
  font-family: var(--font-heading);
  font-size: 2rem;
  margin-top: 3rem;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  color: var(--color-gold-antique);
  position: relative;
}

.guidelines-content h2::before {
  content: '§ ';
  color: var(--color-gold-antique);
  opacity: 0.6;
}

.guidelines-content h3 {
  font-family: var(--font-script);
  font-size: 1.3rem;
  margin-top: 2rem;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
}

.guidelines-content p,
.guidelines-content li {
  line-height: 1.8;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.guidelines-content ul,
.guidelines-content ol {
  margin-left: 2rem;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.guidelines-content li {
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}

/* Section Dividers */
.section-divider {
  margin: 2.5rem 0;
  border: 0;
  height: 1px;
  background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, var(--color-burgundy), transparent);
  opacity: 0.3;
}

/* FAQ Controls */
.faq-controls {
  display: flex;
  gap: 1rem;
  justify-content: flex-end;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.faq-control-btn {
  font-family: var(--font-label);
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
  background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
  color: var(--color-gold-antique);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-gold-antique);
  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
}

.faq-control-btn:hover {
  background-color: var(--color-gold-antique);
  color: var(--color-bg-primary);
}

/* FAQ Section */
.faq-section {
  margin-bottom: 3rem;
}

.faq-section h3 {
  font-family: var(--font-heading);
  font-size: 1.5rem;
  margin-top: 2.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  color: var(--color-gold-honey);
  border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-burgundy);
  padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.faq-section h3:first-of-type {
  margin-top: 0;
}

.faq-item {
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  border: 1px solid var(--color-burgundy);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  overflow: hidden;
  background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
}

.faq-question {
  width: 100%;
  text-align: left;
  font-family: var(--font-script);
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
  border: none;
  cursor: pointer;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
  position: relative;
}

.faq-question::after {
  content: '+';
  font-size: 1.5rem;
  color: var(--color-gold-antique);
  font-weight: bold;
  transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  margin-left: 1rem;
}

.faq-question:hover {
  background-color: rgba(139, 58, 58, 0.1);
  color: var(--color-gold-honey);
}

.faq-item.active .faq-question::after {
  content: '−';
  transform: rotate(180deg);
}

.faq-answer {
  max-height: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
  transition: max-height 0.3s ease, padding 0.3s ease;
  padding: 0 1.5rem;
  background-color: var(--color-bg-primary);
}

.faq-item.active .faq-answer {
  max-height: 1000px;
  padding: 1.5rem;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--color-burgundy);
}

.faq-answer p { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
.faq-answer p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

.faq-answer ul {
  margin-left: 1.5rem;
  margin-top: 0.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.faq-answer li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
.faq-answer a { color: var(--color-gold-antique); text-decoration: underline; }
.faq-answer a:hover { color: var(--color-gold-honey); }
.faq-answer strong { color: var(--color-gold-honey); }

/* Blockquotes */
blockquote {
  border-left: 3px solid var(--color-gold-antique);
  margin: 2rem 0;
  font-style: italic;
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  background-color: var(--color-bg-secondary);
  padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
}

/* Contact Buttons */
.contact-buttons {
  margin-top: 2rem;
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
  text-align: center;
}
</style>

<script>
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
  const faqItems = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item');
  const expandAllBtn = document.getElementById('expand-all');
  const collapseAllBtn = document.getElementById('collapse-all');

  faqItems.forEach(item => {
    const question = item.querySelector('.faq-question');
    if (question) {
      question.addEventListener('click', () => {
        item.classList.toggle('active');
      });
    }
  });

  if (expandAllBtn) {
    expandAllBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      faqItems.forEach(item => item.classList.add('active'));
    });
  }

  if (collapseAllBtn) {
    collapseAllBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      faqItems.forEach(item => item.classList.remove('active'));
    });
  }
});
</script>
